cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper is about accelerating the training of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) by sparsifying activation gradients. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to the design and analysis of algorithms for learning from data. The paper also involves image classification tasks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for reducing computational cost, which could be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and optimization, which could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
